00:25:58,195 --> 00:26:03,299
And there's something really satisfying about that.

514
00:26:03,299 --> 00:26:03,499
And so.

515
00:26:04,658 --> 00:26:07,099
That'll come up later, I'm gonna mention that in a bit.

516
00:26:07,099 --> 00:26:09,960
But what we missed when we were planning this,

517
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:11,480
so everything you just saw in that,

518
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:14,241
all those goals on the board,

519
00:26:14,241 --> 00:26:15,581
we got really close to those,

520
00:26:15,581 --> 00:26:16,542
but a couple of things we missed.

521
00:26:16,542 --> 00:26:20,403
And this is important too.

522
00:26:20,403 --> 00:26:22,523
We didn't think about how the floor was gonna transition.

523
00:26:22,523 --> 00:26:26,684
The only point in that movie that's utter magic,

524
00:26:26,684 --> 00:26:29,385
where we're not adhering to the rules,

525
00:26:29,385 --> 00:26:30,806
is when the floor transition happens,

526
00:26:30,806 --> 00:26:32,086
if you notice we faded to black.

527
00:26:33,078 --> 00:26:33,919
We got to that and we were like,

528
00:26:33,919 --> 00:26:35,119
we don't know how we're gonna handle this,

529
00:26:35,119 --> 00:26:36,440
because it's a tech solution as well.

530
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:38,202
And it was just 10 artists in a room.

531
00:26:38,202 --> 00:26:40,924
And so we took a note of that.

532
00:26:40,924 --> 00:26:43,526
We knew we didn't have an answer for it,

533
00:26:43,526 --> 00:26:44,807
and we continued to move on.

534
00:26:44,807 --> 00:26:47,008
We could have gotten bogged down there, we didn't.

535
00:26:47,008 --> 00:26:51,172
But it was also important to have found that question then,

536
00:26:51,172 --> 00:26:54,114
and not find it out eight months later.

537
00:26:54,114 --> 00:26:56,796
And so one of the other things we didn't really know

538
00:26:56,796 --> 00:26:59,358
how we were going to solve was the interior fog of war.

539
00:26:59,663 --> 00:27:01,925
between buildings, inside of buildings,

540
00:27:01,925 --> 00:27:03,686
how do the rooms work, right?

541
00:27:03,686 --> 00:27:08,149
Or exterior fog of war, we at the end,

542
00:27:08,149 --> 00:27:09,930
we just kind of like, we put fog of war in there,

543
00:27:09,930 --> 00:27:11,651
but we didn't, if you notice, it doesn't reveal.

544
00:27:11,651 --> 00:27:15,354
Again, we knew we didn't have an answer for these.

545
00:27:15,354 --> 00:27:16,775
We made notes of them,

546
00:27:16,775 --> 00:27:18,916
and the next thing we did was that drawing.

547
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:25,042
which is pretty close to how our building hiding works now,

548
00:27:25,042 --> 00:27:26,542
even in X2, it's pretty much the same thing.

549
00:27:26,542 --> 00:27:30,764
But this was immediately, as soon as we finished that movie,

550
00:27:30,764 --> 00:27:32,944
concept went right in.

551
00:27:32,944 --> 00:27:34,125
We know we have a problem here.

552
00:27:34,125 --> 00:27:35,665
How do we wanna solve this?

553
00:27:35,665 --> 00:27:37,886
And then we sent it over to the graphics programmers,

554
00:27:37,886 --> 00:27:38,626
this is what we wanna make.

555
00:27:40,778 --> 00:27:43,219
And then Fog of War, we played around with some stuff.

556
00:27:43,219 --> 00:27:47,741
At this point, it was actually a physical thing.

557
00:27:47,741 --> 00:27:50,302
And that had some gameplay issues.

558
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:52,182
So we went to a more traditional Fog of War.

559
00:27:52,182 --> 00:27:54,383
But again, we didn't want it to be black.

560
00:27:54,383 --> 00:27:55,643
We wanted it to have color.

561
00:27:55,643 --> 00:27:58,764
We didn't want the screen to get all the light being sucked out

562
00:27:58,764 --> 00:28:00,125
of it by the blackness of it.

563
00:28:00,125 --> 00:28:04,046
And so we were trying to get a Fog of War that

564
00:28:04,046 --> 00:28:07,327
was complementary to the light environment.

565
00:28:08,733 --> 00:28:11,115
And even though it didn't end up looking like this,

566
00:28:11,115 --> 00:28:12,796
this is kind of the final result

567
00:28:12,796 --> 00:28:14,517
ended up being more like that.

568
00:28:14,517 --> 00:28:16,719
So back to our goals that we had on the wall,

569
00:28:16,719 --> 00:28:19,341
the things that we wrote down the very first day,

570
00:28:19,341 --> 00:28:21,782
everything up there we hit in blue.

571
00:28:21,782 --> 00:28:23,944
The red thing we knew we probably couldn't do,

572
00:28:23,944 --> 00:28:24,684
but we were trying to figure out

573
00:28:24,684 --> 00:28:27,547
how we could maybe get multiple shadows.

574
00:28:28,750 --> 00:28:32,752
And then effects and destructible interior

575
00:28:32,752 --> 00:28:37,935
and exterior, we had in the movie,

576
00:28:37,935 --> 00:28:39,836
but they weren't necessarily gameplay compliant.

577
00:28:39,836 --> 00:28:42,337
We knew we still had to solve those.

578
00:28:42,337 --> 00:28:43,898
But we did pretty good considering

579
00:28:43,898 --> 00:28:44,378
that was our initial list.

580
00:28:44,378 --> 00:28:49,882
And so this came out of it as well.

581
00:28:49,882 --> 00:28:51,943
Like I said, we needed to not just draw a picture

582
00:28:51,943 --> 00:28:53,323
of a farmhouse.

583
00:28:53,323 --> 00:28:54,964
What were the step heights going to be?

584
00:28:54,964 --> 00:28:56,125
What were the railings going to be?

585
00:28:56,682 --> 00:28:58,124
What were the walls going to be?

586
00:28:58,124 --> 00:29:01,868
What were the, how were the walls going to work on the grid?

587
00:29:01,868 --> 00:29:05,212
You know, is there a grid?

588
00:29:05,212 --> 00:29:07,635
You know, what is the wall height going to be?

589
00:29:07,635 --> 00:29:08,315
Door heights?

590
00:29:08,315 --> 00:29:10,258
Window openings?

591
00:29:10,258 --> 00:29:11,059
All that.

592
00:29:11,059 --> 00:29:13,201
And the funniest thing about this is that

593
00:29:13,642 --> 00:29:16,422
This document was made about 10 years ago

594
00:29:16,422 --> 00:29:19,563
and these metrics are pretty much the same metrics

595
00:29:19,563 --> 00:29:23,304
we use in XCOM 2 and have just been kind

596
00:29:23,304 --> 00:29:25,805
of enhanced a little bit more now.

597
00:29:25,805 --> 00:29:29,226
But these are the same exact measurements for the most part.

598
00:29:29,226 --> 00:29:34,508
So one of the other things that came out of the previs,

599
00:29:34,508 --> 00:29:36,548
if you notice I was probably more concerned.

600
00:29:37,478 --> 00:29:39,840
with the presentation than necessarily the aesthetics.

601
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:43,141
I feel like we were kind of in the ballpark on the aesthetics,

602
00:29:43,141 --> 00:29:45,562
but my primary goal was what was the presentation.

603
00:29:45,562 --> 00:29:47,883
And this was the concept of the soldiers

604
00:29:47,883 --> 00:29:49,224
when we rolled into that.

605
00:29:49,224 --> 00:29:51,865
But again, once we made it, readability came into play.

606
00:29:51,865 --> 00:29:54,486
And we were like, can you really read things?

607
00:29:54,486 --> 00:29:57,768
Does it hold up in both cameras, right?

608
00:29:57,768 --> 00:29:59,329
And so that set us down a row where

609
00:29:59,329 --> 00:30:02,090
we wanted to try to mess with the proportions.

610
00:30:02,090 --> 00:30:03,911
And this is where the miniature thing really came in.

611
00:30:03,911 --> 00:30:07,072
And the guy on the right is.

612
00:30:08,131 --> 00:30:10,594
that we ended up shipping in the game for the soldiers,

613
00:30:10,594 --> 00:30:14,618
but we got much more broad, much more chunky.

614
00:30:14,618 --> 00:30:16,380
And we did this for readability reason.

615
00:30:16,380 --> 00:30:18,603
You know, we wanted to read in both cameras

616
00:30:18,603 --> 00:30:21,967
and trying to balance those two things out.

617
00:30:21,967 --> 00:30:24,550
Another thing, you know, our first Potter reveal,

618
00:30:24,550 --> 00:30:26,933
the first time you see an alien was in the movie.

619
00:30:26,933 --> 00:30:28,054
This is what shipped in the game.

620
00:30:30,372 --> 00:30:32,774
We wanted to set up the missions.

621
00:30:32,774 --> 00:30:34,335
This was a big thing for us.

622
00:30:34,335 --> 00:30:37,918
We wanted to establish some tone before you went in

623
00:30:37,918 --> 00:30:42,801
and started blowing things up, right?

624
00:30:42,801 --> 00:30:45,083
We had the dropship come in, in every mission,

625
00:30:45,083 --> 00:30:48,446
and guys exiting, and you got to feel

626
00:30:48,446 --> 00:30:49,246
for the flavor of the map.

627
00:30:49,246 --> 00:30:54,670
This is the gameplay camera in the movie,

628
00:30:54,670 --> 00:30:57,312
and this is what we shipped with.

629
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:01,961
So we had established where all these cameras were going to be,

630
00:31:01,961 --> 00:31:04,021
and those pretty much stuck.

631
00:31:04,021 --> 00:31:05,001
The significant cameras stuck.

632
00:31:05,001 --> 00:31:08,502
And then some of the intangible results,

633
00:31:08,502 --> 00:31:11,022
the things that we ended up getting out of that movie

634
00:31:11,022 --> 00:31:13,503
that we really weren't planning on,

635
00:31:13,503 --> 00:31:15,623
a huge morale increase for the team.

636
00:31:15,623 --> 00:31:17,644
And I'm not just talking about the 10 guys in that room.

637
00:31:17,644 --> 00:31:19,704
And I'm not just talking about the XCOM team.

638
00:31:19,704 --> 00:31:24,245
The whole studio, the morale increase in the studio

639
00:31:24,245 --> 00:31:24,985
was crazy.

640
00:31:24,985 --> 00:31:27,265
We'd never put together anything like this.

641
00:31:28,438 --> 00:31:31,700
You know, it was our art bible for a long time.

642
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:32,921
It was our constitution.

643
00:31:32,921 --> 00:31:34,683
This was how we wanted the game to look.

644
00:31:34,683 --> 00:31:36,604
Anytime anybody didn't know how something

645
00:31:36,604 --> 00:31:38,205
was supposed to look, we said, go look at the movie.

646
00:31:38,205 --> 00:31:39,746
How's that supposed to work?

647
00:31:39,746 --> 00:31:40,707
Go look at the movie.

648
00:31:40,707 --> 00:31:42,408
And in fact, we would check the movie,

649
00:31:42,408 --> 00:31:44,250
be like, okay, this is how it's supposed to be, right?

650
00:31:44,250 --> 00:31:45,551
And we'd double check it.

651
00:31:45,551 --> 00:31:48,333
It ended up being a recruiting tool for us.

652
00:31:48,333 --> 00:31:50,254
We went for so long without being announced

653
00:31:50,254 --> 00:31:53,357
that it was hard, but when we'd bring people in

654
00:31:53,357 --> 00:31:54,658
and say, this is the game we're making.

655
00:31:55,313 --> 00:31:59,197
it was easy to then hire people.

656
00:31:59,197 --> 00:32:02,660
And then it also ended up being an internal marketing tool,

657
00:32:02,660 --> 00:32:04,542
not just with us, but at the publisher,

658
00:32:04,542 --> 00:32:07,545
it ended up being what we pitched to get the game,

659
00:32:07,545 --> 00:32:08,105
to get the IP.

660
00:32:08,105 --> 00:32:13,951
So, we made a prototype after that,

661
00:32:13,951 --> 00:32:14,071
and

662
00:32:15,048 --> 00:32:16,610
It was missing that soldier story stuff

663
00:32:16,610 --> 00:32:17,831
that I was talking about.

664
00:32:17,831 --> 00:32:20,495
It was missing some of the immersion.

665
00:32:20,495 --> 00:32:23,559
Didn't have the feel of that previs movie.

666
00:32:23,559 --> 00:32:26,543
So again, we went back to what we could do fast.

667
00:32:26,543 --> 00:32:27,504
What could we be agile about?

668
00:32:27,504 --> 00:32:29,426
What could we move quickly on?

669
00:32:30,421 --> 00:32:33,322
And we ended up making another Previs movie.

670
00:32:33,322 --> 00:32:35,222
And this time, it's an engine.

671
00:32:35,222 --> 00:32:37,342
Again, at this point, we're over.

672
00:32:37,342 --> 00:32:38,743
We've got our style set.

673
00:32:38,743 --> 00:32:40,343
We've got our characters worked out.

674
00:32:40,343 --> 00:32:41,903
We understand our proportions.

675
00:32:41,903 --> 00:32:44,964
We've got all these tools in the toolbox right now.

676
00:32:44,964 --> 00:32:47,444
And so no more Macs.

677
00:32:47,444 --> 00:32:51,165
We're using Unreal 3 at this point.

678
00:32:51,165 --> 00:32:52,765
And so we made another movie.

679
00:32:52,765 --> 00:32:58,466
Move out and keep your eyes open.

680
00:32:58,466 --> 00:32:58,646
I got it.

681
00:33:34,090 --> 00:33:38,183
Thanks for watching!

682
00:34:54,517 --> 00:34:56,099
animators decided to have a little fun at the end there.

683
00:34:56,099 --> 00:34:59,924
But so, one of the really interesting things about that,

684
00:34:59,924 --> 00:35:02,327
we, you know, we, at this point, we're really pushing it.

685
00:35:02,327 --> 00:35:04,429
We're really pushing the boundaries.

686
00:35:04,429 --> 00:35:07,653
Rush cams, death cams, pod reveals,

687
00:35:07,653 --> 00:35:09,536
how are those going to be?

688
00:35:09,536 --> 00:35:12,720
And, you know, going into it, you know,

689
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:13,341
if I was going to get

690
00:35:14,557 --> 00:35:15,957
30% I would have been happy.

691
00:35:15,957 --> 00:35:18,759
I think we ended up getting a little more than that.

692
00:35:18,759 --> 00:35:20,340
And the reaction from the programming staff was great.

693
00:35:20,340 --> 00:35:21,201
And they saw it, they were like,

694
00:35:21,201 --> 00:35:23,542
yeah, we can do a lot of this.

695
00:35:23,542 --> 00:35:26,424
But a lot of that stuff did permeate into the game.

696
00:35:26,424 --> 00:35:27,564
And it was really useful.

697
00:35:27,564 --> 00:35:29,646
And I think brought back a little bit of immersion

698
00:35:29,646 --> 00:35:31,727
that we were trying to find.

699
00:35:31,727 --> 00:35:36,109
Again, you see pod reveals, how they look,

700
00:35:36,109 --> 00:35:39,051
what the game looks like when you're shooting,

701
00:35:39,051 --> 00:35:40,212
the targeting cameras.

702
00:35:40,212 --> 00:35:43,954
Again, more of the pod reveals and more of the gameplay.

703
00:35:46,393 --> 00:35:47,394
So then that leads us to XCOM 2.

704
00:35:47,394 --> 00:35:50,516
And this was a really different start for us.

705
00:35:50,516 --> 00:35:55,198
A lot of different things happening in this game.

706
00:35:55,198 --> 00:35:58,119
We turned the premise on its head.

707
00:35:58,119 --> 00:35:59,760
It was no longer a defensive game.

708
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:01,661
Now it was an attacking game.

709
00:36:01,661 --> 00:36:03,342
And that was a pretty big deal.

710
00:36:03,342 --> 00:36:04,523
And you were now a resistance.

711
00:36:04,523 --> 00:36:05,303
And it was 20 years in the future.

712
00:36:05,303 --> 00:36:08,925
Oh, and by the way, you lost the last game,

713
00:36:08,925 --> 00:36:10,426
which was a bit of a twist.

714
00:36:12,260 --> 00:36:13,861
The difference in a sequel,

715
00:36:13,861 --> 00:36:15,542
the theme and tone had changed completely.

716
00:36:15,542 --> 00:36:18,184
The desire to push the visual mechanics

717
00:36:18,184 --> 00:36:19,665
proved out in the first game.

718
00:36:19,665 --> 00:36:21,166
We really wanted to push those.

719
00:36:21,166 --> 00:36:24,068
The engine needed to be converted.

720
00:36:24,068 --> 00:36:25,909
We went to real-time lighting,

721
00:36:25,909 --> 00:36:29,672
went to physically-based rendering.

722
00:36:29,672 --> 00:36:30,793
And the design changes were huge.

723
00:36:30,793 --> 00:36:32,174
And again, when I try to make a previs,

724
00:36:32,174 --> 00:36:35,256
I'm trying to actually encapsulate some of those things

725
00:36:35,256 --> 00:36:38,058
that are the most difficult.

726
00:36:38,058 --> 00:36:38,979
Fully procedural maps.

727
00:36:39,846 --> 00:36:42,208
and new gameplay mechanics.

728
00:36:42,208 --> 00:36:46,131
One of the things here too that's probably worth mentioning

729
00:36:46,131 --> 00:36:48,933
is like the procedural maps part of it.

730
00:36:48,933 --> 00:36:50,814
I was working on that while the team was working

731
00:36:50,814 --> 00:36:52,575
on Enemy Within.

732
00:36:52,575 --> 00:36:54,076
And in retrospect, I was probably, I got so wrapped

733
00:36:54,076 --> 00:36:57,099
up in that, that I lost a little bit of my footing

734
00:36:57,099 --> 00:37:01,322
on preparing for the team.

735
00:37:01,322 --> 00:37:05,845
So, one of the things I'll probably do a little different.

736
00:37:05,845 --> 00:37:06,205
But what we knew.

737
00:37:09,219 --> 00:37:11,300
The team was largely intact again.

738
00:37:11,300 --> 00:37:14,321
Our team has been together for 10, 12 years at this point,

739
00:37:14,321 --> 00:37:17,362
for the most part.

740
00:37:17,362 --> 00:37:18,502
We understood the game we were making.

741
00:37:18,502 --> 00:37:22,743
We didn't have to go, well, what is the contemporary equivalent?

742
00:37:22,743 --> 00:37:25,224
The visual mechanics, you needed a pod reveal.

743
00:37:25,224 --> 00:37:29,225
You needed whatever you needed.

744
00:37:29,225 --> 00:37:31,586
You knew how the game was going to work, right?

745
00:37:33,337 --> 00:37:35,719
And you understood the presentation.

746
00:37:35,719 --> 00:37:39,544
If you had a new armor type, you knew you had a reveal for it.

747
00:37:39,544 --> 00:37:45,531
All the communication pipelines remained the same.

748
00:37:45,531 --> 00:37:48,314
And we really understood, now having made the first game,

749
00:37:48,314 --> 00:37:50,396
we dissected it and what we really

750
00:37:50,396 --> 00:37:53,220
needed to do to make a procedural version of it.

751
00:37:55,085 --> 00:37:57,908
So the approach again, we went to simulated gameplay,

752
00:37:57,908 --> 00:38:03,434
an agile attempt again, this time we're in engine.

753
00:38:03,434 --> 00:38:06,997
But unlike before, we're now in the midst

754
00:38:06,997 --> 00:38:09,040
of rebuilding the renderer and the material system.

755
00:38:09,895 --> 00:38:11,736
That was interesting.

756
00:38:11,736 --> 00:38:14,116
We also didn't isolate the team.

757
00:38:14,116 --> 00:38:14,897
We didn't feel the need to.

758
00:38:14,897 --> 00:38:17,757
We also didn't have everybody working on it altogether.

759
00:38:17,757 --> 00:38:18,818
It kind of went through chunks.

760
00:38:18,818 --> 00:38:20,358
So, it went through phases in it.

761
00:38:20,358 --> 00:38:24,479
While we were developing the game and providing content

762
00:38:24,479 --> 00:38:27,780
for the rest of the team, we were busy making the previs

763
00:38:27,780 --> 00:38:33,182
in conjunction with that, which was quite a bit different

764
00:38:33,182 --> 00:38:34,022
and a bit harder.

765
00:38:34,022 --> 00:38:39,343
And then all the assets that we made were game usable.

766
00:38:41,366 --> 00:38:43,266
So, the visual goals.

767
00:38:43,266 --> 00:38:45,647
We really wanted to improve the fidelity of the geometry,

768
00:38:45,647 --> 00:38:48,968
the animation, everything. We wanted to turn everything up.

769
00:38:48,968 --> 00:38:51,468
There were points in Enemy Within

770
00:38:51,468 --> 00:38:56,149
